manual morph lifecycle and install test plan
===========================================

Purpose
-------
Manual validation checklist for the new morph lifecycle, install, uninstall,
hook, and fallback flows.

This file complements the automated test suite. It focuses on end-to-end
session behavior and log inspection with `rg`.


Key paths
---------
Project root:   <your_local_repo>/morph
Binary:         <your_local_repo>/morph/build/morph
Dev launcher:   <your_local_repo>/morph/testing/morph_run
Prod wrapper:   morph-session
Dev wrapper:    /usr/local/bin/morph-dev-session
Default config: <your_local_repo>/morph/testing/morph.conf
User config:    ~/.config/morph/morph.conf
System config:  /etc/morph/morph.conf


Runtime log base
----------------
Default:
  ${XDG_STATE_HOME:-$HOME/.local/state}/morph

Recommended shell helper:
  export LOG_BASE="${XDG_STATE_HOME:-$HOME/.local/state}/morph"

Optional cleanup before a fresh run:
  rm -f "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log "$LOG_BASE"/shutdown_list.nfo


0) Automated baseline
---------------------
Always start here:

  meson setup build --reconfigure
  meson test -C build --print-errorlogs

Expected:
- build regenerates as `morph`
- config and shell-runtime tests pass


1) Resolve-only config/environment check
----------------------------------------
Use this to validate priority handling without starting a full session:

  MORPH_RESOLVE_ONLY=1 ./testing/morph_run

Filter:
  rg -n "Runtime summary|Environment source|Config file path|Managed hook directory|Managed config directory|Compositor binary|Builtin fallback enabled" "$LOG_BASE"/morph-startup.log

Expected:
- startup summary is written
- resolved config path is visible
- environment source is visible
- no compositor session is started


2) Native session through dev launcher
--------------------------------------
Run from a VT/TTY or native compositor test environment:

  ./testing/morph_run

Filter:
  rg -n "Selected session mode|Native Wayland mode detected|Loaded managed portals file|Started xdg-desktop-portal|Set portal variables|Startup hook completed|Compositor exited" "$LOG_BASE"/morph-startup.log

Expected:
- session mode resolves to native
- portal startup runs before user session components
- startup hook completes afterwards


3) Nested session through dev launcher
--------------------------------------
Run inside an existing X11 or Wayland desktop session:

  ./testing/morph_run

Filter:
  rg -n "Selected session mode|Nested mode detected|Nested clients use WAYLAND_DISPLAY|Skipping .*launch_nested|Compositor exited" "$LOG_BASE"/morph-nested-startup.log

Expected:
- session mode resolves to nested-x11 or nested-wayland
- nested socket is logged
- native portal startup is skipped


4) Shutdown flow and shutdown tracker
-------------------------------------
After a normal or abnormal session exit:

Filter logs:
  rg -n "Starting session cleanup|Running user shutdown hook|No user shutdown hook configured or found|Performing dynamic session cleanup|Sent SIGTERM|Forcing SIGKILL|Session cleanup completed" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*-shutdown.log

Inspect tracker:
  cat "$LOG_BASE"/shutdown_list.nfo

Expected:
- `launch` and `launch_nested` entries appear in the tracker
- `launch_nokill` entries do not appear in the tracker
- shutdown log shows cleanup order clearly


5) Reload flow
--------------
Trigger reload from a running morph session:

  ./build/morph --reload-config

Filter:
  rg -n "Starting managed reload hook|Running user reload hook|Sourcing user reload hook file|Reloading |reload_once|Managed reload hook completed" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log

Expected:
- managed reload runtime is entered
- configured or fallback reload hook is visible
- `reload` and `reload_once` actions are logged


6) Hook fallback chain
----------------------
Validate these scenarios:

1. session wrapper with empty user hooks
2. session wrapper with custom user hooks
3. direct binary start with managed wrapper-style hooks
4. direct binary start with explicit custom hooks

Filter:
  rg -n "Running user startup hook|Running default user startup hook|Sourcing user startup hook file|Running user shutdown hook|Running user reload hook|No user .* hook configured or found" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log

Expected:
- managed frame stays active
- fallback order is visible in logs
- missing hooks are reported explicitly, not silently ignored


7) Config priority
------------------
Explicit override:

  MORPH_CONFIG=/path/to/other.conf MORPH_RESOLVE_ONLY=1 ./testing/morph_run

Builtin fallback opt-in:

  MORPH_ALLOW_BUILTIN_FALLBACK=1 MORPH_RESOLVE_ONLY=1 ./testing/morph_run

Filter:
  rg -n "Config file path:|override from MORPH_CONFIG|user config fallback|system config fallback|builtin fallback" "$LOG_BASE"/morph-startup.log

Expected:
- explicit config wins
- user config wins over system config
- builtin fallback appears only with opt-in


8) Environment priority
-----------------------
Caller override example:

  MORPH_DBG=2 MORPH_RESOLVE_ONLY=1 ./testing/morph_run

Filter:
  rg -n "Environment source|MORPH_DBG:|MORPH_X11:|MORPH_X11_DISPLAY:|MORPH_LOG_LEVEL:|Crash handler enabled:" "$LOG_BASE"/morph-startup.log

Expected:
- caller environment wins over sourced files
- selected runtime values are visible in the summary


9) Dev install helper
---------------------
Print helper output:

  ./scripts/dev-install.sh install --print-sudo-help

Create local launcher link:

  ./scripts/dev-install.sh install --link-launcher

Remove local launcher link:

  ./scripts/dev-install.sh uninstall --link-launcher

Expected:
- existing real files are preserved
- warnings clearly explain what stays untouched
- sudo help prints the dev-session commands for `/usr/local/bin` and `/usr/share/wayland-sessions`


10) Production install and uninstall
------------------------------------
Inspect install manifest:

  meson introspect --installed build

Conservative uninstall preview:

  ./scripts/system-uninstall.sh --builddir build

Conservative uninstall with removal:

  sudo ./scripts/system-uninstall.sh --builddir build --remove

Expected:
- manifest lists installed morph artifacts
- print-only mode does not remove anything
- remove mode deletes only unchanged files
- modified files are reported and left in place


11) Session desktop files
-------------------------
Inspect session entries:

  grep -nE '^(Name|Exec|TryExec)=' sessions/morph.desktop sessions/morph-dev.desktop

Expected:
- `sessions/morph.desktop` uses `morph-session`
- `sessions/morph-dev.desktop` uses `/usr/local/bin/morph-dev-session`


12) Crash/error path
--------------------
If you intentionally provoke a failing session:

Filter:
  rg -n "crashed or exited with an error|triggering managed shutdown runtime|Check the detailed crash log|error-scan" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log

Expected:
- startup log records the failure
- managed shutdown fallback is visible on abnormal exit
- crash summary points to relevant log data


Useful combined filters
-----------------------
Startup overview:

  rg -n "Runtime summary|Selected session mode|Config file path|Environment source|Managed hook|Managed config|Portal|Startup hook completed|Compositor exited" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log

Shutdown overview:

  rg -n "Starting session cleanup|Running user shutdown hook|dynamic session cleanup|Sent SIGTERM|Forcing SIGKILL|Session cleanup completed" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*-shutdown.log

Warnings, errors, and fallbacks:

  rg -n "fallback|WARN|ERROR|No user .* hook configured|skipping|invalid MORPH_" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log

Reload-specific view:

  rg -n "Starting managed reload hook|Reloading |reload_once|Managed reload hook completed" "$LOG_BASE"/morph*.log


